04484.title: My Kitchen Rules New Zealand
04484.description:
After five hugely successful seasons in Australia, the smash-hit cooking competition My Kitchen Rules crosses the Tasman for the first time ever.
My Kitchen Rules New Zealand pits pairs of home cooks against each other, competing for a grand prize of $100,000.
The series begins by taking the viewer on a culinary journey around the country. Ordinary New Zealanders cooking in Kiwi kitchens will transform regular homes into instant restaurants for one pressure-cooker night.
Ten pairs of cooks split into two groups will each battle it out against the clock to prepare their best three-course meal.  It’s kitchen against kitchen, and guess who’s coming to dinner?
Not only their competitors, but two of the country’s most celebrated chefs.
The My Kitchen Rules New Zealand judges are Ben Bayly, executive chef of The Grove and Baduzzi, and winner of Cuisine magazine’s 2014 Chef of the Year award, and Gareth Stewart, executive chef of Soul Bar and Bistro.
“I’m hoping these contestants will put their personalities on a plate in some well-practised, home-cooked meals,” says Ben.
“I’m really looking forward to getting around New Zealand and into the contestants’ homes and I’m especially looking forward to some outstanding food,” adds Gareth.
Along with the other teams, Ben and Gareth will taste, judge and award points for each meal.  The lowest-scoring pair in each group will then be eliminated.  
But that’s just the start.  In the following episodes, there are plenty of twists in store for the remaining contestants – including another, unexpected instant restaurant round with some surprise challengers.  
Then the competition switches to a new series of challenges:  ‘People’s Choice’ challenges on location, where members of the public vote for the dishes and teams they like best, then ‘Rapid Cook-Off’, ‘Showdown’ and ‘Sudden Death’ challenges at the My Kitchen Rules headquarters, in which each week winning teams can secure immunity, but losing teams face elimination.
Location challenges include cooking for 100 children and their families at Auckland Hospital’s Ronald McDonald House, feeding 150 people at an international market day on Auckland’s waterfront, feeding a gang of bikers and cooking pizza for the public outside Sky City.


Guest judges include international chef and author of Me’a Kai: The Food and Flavours of the South Pacific, Robert Oliver, head chef of award-winning Auckland restaurant The Grill, Sean Connolly, MasterChef New Zealand winner, dietician and nutritionist, Nadia Lim, and MasterChef USA contestant and chef, Grace Ramirez.
On the steep climb towards the Grand Final, the standard of cooking will rise and rise.  This is home-cooking like you’ve never seen it before, judged by some of the country’s best chefs.
But My Kitchen Rules’ point of difference is that it is as much about the personalities of the cooks as it is about their food.  There’s a wide range of pairs of home cooks from around the country, including modern-day hippies from the Waikato, ‘bogan besties’ from Tauranga, social media buddies from central Auckland, newlyweds from Dunedin, a fireman and his ‘flame’ from Lower Hutt, sisters from Hawkes Bay, a Cook Island and Maori couple from Palmerston North, corporate dads from Auckland’s North Shore, young gym junkies from Christchurch, Laotian-born friends who are experts in Asian cuisine and a flamboyant former model and photographer from Orewa and the North Shore known as ‘Beauty and the Beast’.
This mix of strangers thrown together under pressure produces intense rivalry and conflict, peppered with plenty of comedy along the way.  The viewers will soon find the contestants they love, and those they love to hate – and it’s those allegiances and antipathies that make My Kitchen Rules so compelling.

0300007945.description: Catch all the excitement of a sporting event mixed with the skill and passion required to create an innovative culinary masterpiece.

0300009625.title: Ottolenghi's Mediterranean Feast
0300009625.description: Chef Ottolenghi explores the history and culture of locales along the Mediterranean through its local cuisine and rustles up a selection of dishes.

0300009015.title: The Chef's Bar
0300009015.description: In each episode, an epic meal, crafted before your eyes by culinary stars Craig Harding and Rob Rossi, feeds a fascinating, eclectic trio of guests.

0300008706.title: Chef Eric's Culinary Classroom
0300008706.description: Join world-renowned Chef Eric Crowley for his first Masterclass video series inspiring you to feel confident in the kitchen with spectacular dishes.

0300010267.title: Cake Boss
0300010267.description: Take a peek into the operations of Carlo's Bake Shop, where you'll find family, relationships, drama, and the most spectacular cakes ever made.

0300010386.title: Winner Cake All
0300010386.description: America's top cake-baking teams craft extraordinary and intricate cake toppers and themed displays as they compete for a $10,000 prize.

0300006038.title: Pitchin' In
0300006038.description: An executive chef at New York’s Four Seasons hit the road to to cook up regional dishes with food producers, from lobster fisherman to hog farmers.

04880.title: Eat Your Way to Wellness
04880.description: A physician’s assistant and culinary medicine expert covers many health topics, giving practical advice on the relationship between food and wellness.

0300000059.title: South Africa With Gregg Wallace
0300000059.description: Culinary expert Gregg Wallace sets off to explore South Africa's most beloved landscapes and experiences, along with its glorious food.

03565.title: Fluffy's Food Adventures
03565.description: Gabriel "Fluffy" Iglesias and his comedy crew search for the most mouthwatering dishes in America, discovering local gems and a few celebrities.

0300008204.title: Breaking Bread With Brooke Burke
0300008204.description: The multifaceted TV personality brings you to visit her famous friends, at their homes or restaurants, sharing food and recipes close to their hearts.

0300000262.title: Food Safari
0300000262.description: Embark on a culinary journey across Australia to learn about the country’s diverse cuisines from acclaimed chefs and passionate homecooks.

01806.title: Chef Michael's Kitchen
01806.description: Chef Michael is going back to basics with a twist! Step inside his kitchen where he will share his favorite home-style recipes, ingredients and cooking techniques, while teaching the viewer how to stir in their own personality.

0300006359.title: Martin Yan's Chinatowns
0300006359.description: Host Martin Yan shows off some of his favorite Chinese recipes while exploring many Chinatown neighborhoods in cities around the globe.

0300009160.title: Positively Paula
0300009160.description: Paula Deen invites you into her home for a one-on-one experience while she cooks her favorite recipes, sharing memories and her heart.

0300007085.title: Wine, Dine and Stein
0300007085.description: Chef Jack Stein travels with his family to find the ultimate pairings with wine and food.

0300009585.title: Tom Kerridge's Best Ever Dishes
0300009585.description: Noted Michelin-starred chef Tom Kerridge demonstrates how to cook delicious versions of the various kinds of food people love to eat.

0300005153.title: Hawaii Cooks With Roy Yamaguchi
0300005153.description: While searching for new flavors and influences, a renowned chef brings meals to life with incredible recipes that evoke the eclectic spirit of Hawaii.

01736.title: Chef's Protege
01736.description: The Chef's Protege is a 2013 BBC Two television series that follows three Michelin star chefs becoming mentors, as they return to their old catering colleges to select and train a protégé.

0300005167.title: Graham Kerr's Kitchen
0300005167.description: From ultra-burgers and veggie burgers to savory toppings for your side dishes, here’s a cooking show with healthy and tasty ideas for any meal.

02039.title: Famous Food
02039.description: Seven Celebrities, with a taste for entrepreneurship and an appetite for success, demonstrate how they are hungry enough to open a hip, new Hollywood restaurant right on the famous Sunset Strip.

0300009014.title: Rustic Adventures: Argentina
0300009014.description: Season 2 of the food, travel, and adventure show leads the inspiration-seeking chefs to scenic Argentina, from the pampas to the peaks of the Andes.

0300008647.title: Lidia Celebrates America
0300008647.description: Host Lidia Bastianich gets a taste of the wide array of American culture and food as she meets with families and special celebrity guests.

0270.title: Hey Kids Let's Cook
0270.description: Hey Kids Let's Cook is an innovative cooking show, based on nutrition, created just for kids and teens.

0300007562.title: Now Eat This! With Rocco Dispirito
0300007562.description: When celebrity chef Rocco DiSpirito meets families who long to incorporate healthier food into their lifestyle, he helps them complete their goals.

0300000126.title: Dinner Date: South Africa
0300000126.description: One lucky single gets the chance to find love—or at least a second date—over three meals prepared for them in their home by three different suitors.

0300006367.title: Baking It Easy
0300006367.description: Whether you’re a rookie pastry chef or you can make pie with your eyes closed, this dessert show will teach you how to improve your culinary skills.

0195.title: Rachel Allen Home Cooking
0195.description: Rachel Allen: Home Cooking is about the very best of cooking at home, so we got to film inside the home kitchens of some of the most amazing chefs.

03320.title: Hell's Kitchen
03320.description: Renowned restauranteur Gordon Ramsay hosts a fierce competition for aspiring chefs, as they vie for a prestigious job at one of his eateries.

0300009227.title: A Mouth Full of Sin
0300009227.description: You never know what your host will say next in this edgy cooking show that combines education, comedy, and deliciously full-flavored food.

0300007524.title: Planet Chef
0300007524.description: Professional chefs, all trained in France, go on a cooking journey back to their native homelands in locales as varied as Tunisia, Greece, and Mexico.

0300008502.title: Eating in With Lidia
0300008502.description: Chef Lidia Bastianich democratizes gourmet cooking with easy-to-follow recipes using ingredients already in the pantry or that won’t break the bank.

04601.title: Comfort Eating
04601.description: A comedian with a big appetite goes on a guilt-free gastronomic tour of Britain, visiting a new location for each 24-hour period of eating.

0300009846.title: River Cottage: Australia
0300009846.description: Former Tasmanian chef Paul West will face new challenges and uniquely Australian characters as he attempts to set up his own functioning farm.

0300010400.title: @Home With Tori
0300010400.description: Step into the home of haute hostess Tori Spelling as she puts her unique spin on dishes, creating “TORIfied” meals and drinks for friends and family.

0300005862.title: Cook's Country
0300005862.description: Discover the best regional home cooking in the country, where family-friendly recipes from every corner of America are reimagined for home cooks.

0300009940.title: Making Bread
0300009940.description: In this series hosted by NFL quarterback and crypto enthusiast Matt Barkley, we help you make sense of making money in today's world.

04566.title: Duncan's Thai Kitchen
04566.description: Cooking adventures meets living history in this series as a chef and culinary arts teacher captures the flavors and essence of Thailand on-location.

0300007670.title: Guga Foods
0300007670.description: The Miami chef behind @realguga on TikTok shares mouth-watering recipes, cooking techniques, and inventive experiments for his meat-loving audience.

0300009204.title: Iron Chef (Español)
0300009204.description: "Iron Chef" es una innovadora competencia de cocina de Japón que combina la emoción de una competencia deportiva uno a uno con la cocina gourmet.

0300008291.title: Burger Scholar Session
0300008291.description: First We Feast presents burger scholar George Motz, who teaches you everything and every method you need to know about cooking regional hamburgers.

0300007087.title: Sarah Graham: Food Safari
0300007087.description: South African food blogger and cookbook author Sarah Graham takes her traveling kitchen on a food safari through Zimbabwe, Zambia and South Africa.

0300007117.title: Crime Scene Kitchen
0300007117.description: Bakers must decode what type of dessert was made using just crumbs and a few elusive clues.

0300008734.title: Julia Child - Cooking With Master Chefs
0300008734.description: The iconic PBS series starring Julia Child and master chefs will give you great ideas from poultry to lobster souffle and even hot chocolate truffles!

0300009583.title: Tom Kerridge's Proper Pub Food
0300009583.description: In this cooking show, noted Michelin-starred chef Tom Kerridge shows how to cook classic British pub food at home for everyone to enjoy.

0300009133.title: MasterChef UK
0300009133.description: Some of the best amateur cooks in Britain show off their technical skills and compete for the top spot by progressing through a series of challenges.

0300008073.title: All the Best with Zita Keeley
0300008073.description: Zita Keeley is your host and guide for this culinary travel show where she partakes of delicious foods and plenty of cocktails all over the world.

0300009643.title: Vegan Mashup
0300009643.description: Three award-winning chefs and very special guests put a healthy, modern spin on plant-based cooking as they whip up easy and delicious vegan meals.

0300009829.title: Foodie Road Trip with Skye Estroff
0300009829.description: Connect with Americans from all walks of life through delicious local food that celebrates all that is colorful and unique about small towns.

0300008700.title: Baking With Julia
0300008700.description: Together with some of the country's best pastry chefs and bakers, Julia Child shares techniques, time-honored tips, and meticulously tested recipes.

04736.title: Tastes Like Home
04736.description: Join chef Catherine Fulvio as she journeys to different parts of Ireland to help families give their loved ones some "home cooking.”

0300005068.title: Ramsay's Kitchen Nightmares
0300005068.description: A brilliant chef who never holds his tongue, Gordon Ramsay visits struggling restaurants around the UK and shows them how to turn the ship around.

0300006184.title: Struggle Meals
0300006184.description: In this inspiring cooking show, you don't need to have fancy kitchen equipment or a huge budget to make delicious and simple dishes.

0300009877.title: Fresh Market Dinners
0300009877.description: This traveling cooking series takes the audience on a Canadian culinary journey from market to plate, using fresh produce and artisanal ingredients.

0300006010.title: Gordon Ramsay's Festive Home Cooking
0300006010.description: In this short series, Gordon Ramsay invites us into his home to show it’s still possible for even the busiest person to cook stunning family food.

0300009080.title: Almazan Kitchen
0300009080.description: Dive into the magical surroundings of Serbian forests and enjoy the most epic foodporn you will ever see, along with the best recipes from the world.

0300009279.title: Born to Cook
0300009279.description: Quick, charming, and ever-so deprecatingly British, Jack Stein has recently taken charge of the nine restaurants under the Stein brand.

0300009903.title: Holiday Eatz
0300009903.description: Hosted by chef Kimberly Lallouz, this series marks all the holidays with unique, multi-course party menus that are easy to make and sure to impress.

0300007754.title: At the Chef's Table
0300007754.description: A coast-to-coast culinary tour of America's most celebrated eateries with behind-the-scenes access to the personal lives of their celebrity chefs.
